FBIS4-19120 "drweu072_b_94007" FBIS-WEU-94-072 Daily Report 11 Apr 1994 BENELUX Netherlands CDA Leader Brinkman Suspected of Knowledge of Tax Fraud CDA Leader Brinkman Suspected of Knowledge of Tax Fraud BR1304122194 Rotterdam NRC HANDELSBLAD in Dutch 11 Apr 94 p 1 BR1304122194 Rotterdam NRC HANDELSBLAD Dutch BFN [Unattributed article: "Brinkman Intends To Stay On in Controversial Job"] [Excerpt] Elco Brinkman, CDA [Christian Democratic Appeal Party] leader, for the time being, will stay on as a board member of Arscop BV, a company that manages the accounts of a firm whose management is suspected of tax fraud. When the company was raided a pistol was also found. "I am in contact with my fellow board members about this situation and the accusation that has been made," Brinkman said last weekend. In a program broadcast Friday evening [8 April] on the KRO [Catholic Radio Broadcasting Company] series "Reporter," it was maintained that Brinkman must have known about the alleged fraud. [passage omitted]
